{"spanId":"sp-29","stage":"RELEASE_GATE","kind":"APPROVAL","name":"Human approves the branch; blocked while high-risk assumptions are open","outcome":"APPROVE","detail":"Read all five findings. The two MEDIUM are real and must be fixed before merge: UriComponentsBuilder instead of string concatenation, and split the exception handler so IOException from QR generation isn't conflated with unrelated IO failures. The three LOW I accept for a branch — shortCode is bounded by service.resolve(), the ByteArrayOutputStream close is a non-issue on a heap buffer, and rate limiting is explicitly out of scope. Blocking issue not in the findings: the code imports com.google.zxing but the pom.xml change was refused by policy, so this will not compile as proposed. Approving to a branch only, not to merge — the dependency must be added by a human first.","durationMillis":54066,"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cached":false,"at":1784293574.419440000}
